text: Wenceslas I, Duke of Saxe-Wittenberg ( – 15 May 1388, in Celle) was an Elector of Saxony and a Prince of Lüneburg. He was the son of Rudolf I and his 3rd wife, Agnes of Lindow-Ruppin. Category:1337 births Category:1388 deaths Category:Princes of Lüneburg
title: Wenceslas I, Duke of Saxe-Wittenberg
